revision.text:
'''Abortion in Estonia''' has been legal since 23 November 1955, when [[Estonia]] was part of the [[Soviet Union]]. Estonia fine-tuned their legislation after the restoration of independence.<ref name="un">[https://www.un.org/esa/population/publications/abortion/doc/estoni1.doc Estonia - ABORTION POLICY - United Nations]</ref>

Estonia allows [[abortion]] on-demand for any purpose,<ref name="un" /> before the end the 11th week of [[pregnancy]].<ref name="riigiteataja">{{cite web |url=https://www.riigiteataja.ee/akt/13243384 |title= Raseduse katkestamise ja steriliseerimise seadus |date= 25 November 1998 |publisher = [[Elektrooniline Riigi Teataja]] |language = Estonian }}</ref> Later abortions are permitted up to the 21st week (included) if the woman is younger than 15 years old or older than 45 years old, if the pregnancy endangers the woman's health, if the child may have a serious [[Physical disability|physical]] or [[Mental disability (disambiguation)|mental defect]], or if the woman's illness or other medical problem hinders the child's development.<ref name="riigiteataja" />

Women who want to have an abortion for personal reasons not specified in the abortion legislation will be expected to pay a fee according to the abortion provider's price list.<ref name="un" /> Abortion performed for medical reasons is covered for insured persons by the Estonian Health Insurance Fund.<ref name="haigekassa">{{cite web|url=http://www.haigekassa.ee/kysi?q=16222 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727091417/http://www.haigekassa.ee/kysi?q=16222 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=27 July 2011 |title=abort - haigekassa.ee |date=28 February 2011 |publisher=Estonian Health Insurance Fund |language=Estonian }}</ref>

38.7% of pregnancies ended in abortion in Estonia in 2006, a decline from 49.4% just six years before.<ref name="rate">[http://www.johnstonsarchive.net/policy/abortion/estonia/ab-estoniac2.html Estonia: abortion rates by county, 2000-2006]</ref>

In 2010, there were 9087 abortions in Estonia, which meant 57.4 abortions for every hundred live births.<ref>"[http://uudised.err.ee/index.php?06232180 Abortide arv langeb jätkuvalt]". [[Eesti Rahvusringhääling|ERR]].</ref> {{as of|2010}}, the abortion rate was 25.5 abortions per 1000 women aged 15-44 years. <ref name="un2013">{{Cite web | title = World Abortion Policies 2013 | publisher = United Nations | year = 2013 | url = https://www.un.org/en/development/desa/population/publications/policy/world-abortion-policies-2013.shtml | accessdate = 3 March 2014 }}</ref>

[[Mifepristone]] (medical abortion) was registered in 2003.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://gynuity.org/resources/read/llist-of-mifepristone-approval-en/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2017-09-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926164348/http://gynuity.org/resources/read/llist-of-mifepristone-approval-en |archive-date=2017-09-26 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
