{{Infobox person |image = Janet_O'Sullivan.jpg |imagesize = 250px |name = Janet O'Sullivan |other_names = Janet Ní Shuilleabháin |nationality = Irish |known for = [[Pro-choice]] campaigning |website = {{URL|http://janet.ie/}} }}
'''Janet O'Sullivan''' is a [[pro-choice]] campaigner in [[Ireland]]. She is a former spokesperson for the [[Abortion Rights Campaign]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1-SOWV7bb4o|date=22 September 2016|title=Abortion in Ireland|publisher=[[BBC World News]]}}</ref> She publishes under both the Irish version of her name, '''Janet Ní Shuilleabháin''', and the English version '''Janet O'Sullivan'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://standardissuemagazine.com/author/josullivan/|title=Author Bio|publisher=Standard Issue Magazine}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/author/janet-o-sullivan|publisher=Independent UK|title=UK Author Bio}}</ref> In 2016, the [[BBC]] included her in the list of [[100 Women (BBC)|100 Women]] for "inspirational and influential women for 2016"<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[BBC]]|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-38012048|title=BBC 100 Women 2016: Who's on the list|date=21 November 2016}}</ref>
== Campaigning == O'Sullivan has been a pro-choice believer since the early 1990s, when the [[X Case]] made the news, and had an abortion herself a few years later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mic.com/articles/82271/woman-takes-over-ireland-twitter-account-and-tells-powerful-story-about-her-abortion#.jNLyXiy1g|title=Ireland Twitter Account abortion story}}</ref> As the spokesperson for the Abortion Rights Campaign, she has frequently written in national newspapers, and appeared on radio and TV about the abortion debate in Ireland.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/life/insults-and-abuse-debate-that-divides-nation-like-no-other-34865898.html|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]|title=Insults and abuse: debate that divides nation like no other|page=44|date=9 July 2016|accessdate=26 September 2016|first=John|last=Meagher}}</ref>
O'Sullivan is also a Bi-Visibility activist who has campaigned for Marriage Equality.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://anarchism.pageabode.com/andrewnflood/marriage-equality-critical-anarchism-dabf2015|title=Marriage Equality}}</ref><ref>{{cite episode|series=Ireland AM|title=Dealing with bisexuality|url=http://www.tv3.ie/ireland_am_video.php?locID=1.65.74&video=75655|station=[[TV3 (Ireland)|TV3]]|date=3 February 2016}}</ref>
=== Referendum on the Eighth Amendment === {{see also|Eighth Amendment of the Constitution of Ireland|Abortion in the Republic of Ireland|Thirty-sixth Amendment of the Constitution Bill 2018}}
O'Sullivan was in favour of the repeal of the [[Eighth Amendment of the Constitution of Ireland|Eighth Amendment]] and is working towards the goal of repealing the amendment and introducing legislation both in Ireland and Northern Ireland which ensures that women have the right to choose.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abortionrightscampaign.ie/about-arc/|title=Goals of the campaign}}</ref> On April 3, 2018 she registered as a third party with [[Standards in Public Office Commission|SIPO]], the Irish government ethics watchdog. She was the only individual person to register as a third party.<ref>{{cite web|title=Register of Third Parties|url=http://www.sipo.ie/en/Reports/Register-of-Third-Parties/|publisher=Standards in Public Office Commission|accessdate=17 April 2018}}</ref>
