{{Infobox body of water | name = Jus Reservoir | native_name = Takungan Jus | native_name_lang = ms | other_name = | image = Jus Reservoir.JPG | alt = | caption = | image_bathymetry = | alt_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Jasin District|Jasin]], [[Melaka]], [[Malaysia]] | group = | coordinates = {{Coord|2|26|25.9|N|102|23|01.4|E|region:MY_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}} | type = [[Reservoir]] | etymology = | part_of = | inflow = | rivers = | outflow = | oceans = | catchment = | basin_countries = | agency = | designation = | date-built = 2000 | engineer = | date-flooded = 2003 | length = | width = | area ={{convert|5.5|km2}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = {{convert|43000000000|liters}} | residence_time = | salinity = | shore = | elevation = | temperature_high = | temperature_low = | frozen = | islands = | islands_category = | sections = | trenches = | benches = | cities = | pushpin_map = <!-- the name of a location map as per Template:Location map. Requires coordinates= parameter to display map. --> | pushpin_label_position = <!-- left, right, top or bottom --> | pushpin_map_alt = | pushpin_map_caption = | website = | reference = }}
The '''Jus Reservoir''' ({{lang-ms|Takungan Jus}}) is a [[reservoir]] in [[Jasin District]], [[Melaka]], [[Malaysia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.therakyatpost.com/news/2014/04/10/learning-efficient-water-supply-management-from-malacca/|title=Learning efficient water supply management from Malacca|work=The Rakyat Post}}</ref>
==History== The construction of the dam and reservoir started in 2000 to address the water needs of Malacca. The reservoir and the dam started its operation in 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.bharian.com.my/articles/BekalanairMelakamencukupihadapimusimkemarau/Article/ |title=Berita Harian - Bekalan air Melaka mencukupi hadapi musim kemarau |work=bharian.com.my |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150710223812/http://www2.bharian.com.my/articles/BekalanairMelakamencukupihadapimusimkemarau/Article/ |archivedate=2015-07-10 |df= }}</ref>
==Geography== The dam is capable of storing 43 billion litres of water over an area of 5.5&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> in an overall area of 23&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup>. The raw water supply for the reservoir is channeled from [[Durian Tunggal Reservoir]], [[Kesang River]] and [[Batang Melaka River]]. The water from the reservoir goes to the water treatment facilities in [[Merlimau]] and [[Durian Tunggal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/story/?file=%2F2010%2F3%2F1%2Fsouthneast%2F5758086&sec=southneast%7ctitle=Archives%7cwork=thestar.com.my|title=Archives|work=thestar.com.my}}</ref>
