The '''Muskoka Initiative on Maternal, Newborn and Child Health''' is a funding initiative announced at the [[36th G8 summit]] which commits [[G8|member nations]] to collectively spend an additional $5 billion between 2010 and 2015 to accelerate progress toward the achievement of [[Millennium Development Goals]] 4 and 5, the reduction of [[Maternal death|maternal]], [[infant mortality|infant]] and [[child mortality]] in [[developing countries]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Text of the G8 Summit communique: Muskoka Declaration|url=http://www.ctv.ca/CTVNews/Politics/20100626/text-of-the-g8-communique/|publisher=[[CTV.ca]]|accessdate=26 June 2010}}</ref>  A second summit on Maternal, Newborn and Child Health was held in Toronto from May 28-30, 2014 in follow-up to the original 36th G8 summit.<ref>{{cite web|title=Maternal, Newborn and Child Health (MNCH) Summit|url=http://mnch.international.gc.ca/index-en.html|publisher=Government of Canada|accessdate=30 May 2014}}</ref>

